gel is the potential Aquinas of Protestantism. Exploring Hegel's philosophy of spirit in historical, cultural, and personal religious context, the book identifies Hegel's relationship with Hölderlin and his response to Hölderlin's madness as key elements in the philosopher's religious and philosophical development, especially with respect to the meaning of transcendence and dialectic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aSpiritxHistoryy19th century. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh  aAbraham (biblical figure).  aAbsolute Encompassing.  aAll-Comprehensive.  aAnabasis (Xenophon).  aAsendorf, Ulrich.  aAugsburg Confession.  aBattle of Jena.  aBenedict, Saint.  aBuddhism (Buddha).  aCalvinism.  aCarus, Carl Gustav.  aConsciousness-itself.  aDante.  aDescombes, Vincent.  aDickey, Lawrence.  aEbeling, Gerhard.  aEleatics.  aEnlightenment, European.  aErasmus, Desiderius.  aFackenheim, Emil.  aFranciscans.  aGenesis, Book of.  aGnosticism.  aGregory of Nyssa.  aHartmann, Klaus.  aHohenzollerns.  aHöfener, Heiner.  aIncarnation.  aJoachim of Fiore.  aKazantzakis, Nikos.  aKnowledge, Absolute.  aLebenspraxis.  aLukacs, George.  aLutheran Confessions.  aMarxism.  aMelissus.  aNational Socialism.  aParmenides.  aPelagianism.  aPhilo of Alexandria.  aPindar.  abiblicism.  achristomonism.  aecclesiology.  aempiricism.  afeminism.  aillness, Hegel on.  amonism.  aneo-Romanticism.  anihilism.  aontotheology.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400832316zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400832316423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781400832316/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESS